cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with compressive sensing and the convergence of CoSaMP and Subspace Pursuit algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also involves mathematical manipulations and sufficient conditions, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deals with algorithms and models for learning from data. Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with algorithms and their performance, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
